title: Thursday Briefing: U.S. Soldier Is Out of North Korea
description: Plus the new ChatGPT can ‘see’ and ‘talk.’

title: Germany Toughens Migration Checks to Control Asylum Seeker Influx
description: With the number of asylum seekers rising, along with support for the far right, the government has come under increasing pressure to act.

title: Germany Cracks Down on Another Far-Right Group
description: The raids were the second such action in about a week and came about 10 months after the authorities foiled what they described as a far-right plot to topple the government.

title: United Nations Struggles to Meet Challenge of Changing World
description: Most everyone agrees on the need for changes, but there is little agreement on what to do and nearly insuperable hurdles to doing anything.

title: Official Visits Between Saudi Arabia and Israel Highlight Warming Ties
description: Israel’s tourism minister went to Saudi Arabia, and a Saudi envoy toured the Israeli-occupied West Bank. The trips reflected how the two countries are moving toward normalizing their relationship.

title: Russia-Ukraine War: Ukraine’s Influence Increases in Disputed Black Sea Waters
description: Several ships have sailed a new shipping corridor established to evade Russia’s de facto blockade. A military campaign has helped Ukraine gain some control, experts say.

title: The Tortured Legacy of Yambo Ouologuem
description: Five decades ago, an award-winning Malian author disappeared from public life after being accused of plagiarism. Now, his ambiguous novel is being released, and evaluated, in new light.

title: Russia Shares New Video of Black Sea Fleet Admiral Ukraine Claims to Have Killed
description: The latest video, and comments published in Russian news outlets, appeared to be an effort by Moscow to end speculation over the admiral’s status.

title: Biden Administration Says Israelis Can Travel to U.S. Without a Visa
description: The U.S. allowed Israel into its visa-waiver program after a summer test run that gave U.S. citizens, including Palestinian Americans, visa-less entry into Israel.

title: North Korea Says It Will Expel Travis King, U.S. Soldier Who Crossed the Border
description: Pvt. Travis T. King dashed across the inter-Korean Demilitarized Zone in July to flee to North Korea.

title: Libya Flooding Disaster Underlines the Country’s Corruption
description: Repair work was agreed but never finished and Derna paid the price. Experts say infrastructure projects have long been neglected, with officials focusing instead on lining their own pockets.

title: Fire at Wedding Hall in Iraq Kills More Than 100 People
description: Eyewitnesses said flares were set off in celebration as the bride and groom danced, and that a fire broke out at astonishing speed.

title: Canadian Speaker in House of Commons Quits After Honoring Ukrainian Who Fought for Nazis
description: Anthony Rota, the speaker of Canada’s House of Commons, introduced a 98-year-old veteran of an SS unit as a “hero” in front of Ukraine’s president.

title: Wednesday Briefing
description: Uncertainty over the fate of a Russian admiral.

title: In Azerbaijan-Armenia Conflict, a Bloody End in Nagorno-Karabakh
description: After decades of wars and tense stalemates, almost no one saw it coming: Azerbaijan seized Nagorno-Karabakh from Armenian control seemingly overnight.

title: Iraq Wedding Hall Fire Kills at Least 100
description: The fire spread quickly in part because the building was made of highly flammable construction materials, state media reported.
